h3. Ingredients

* Â½ Cup mayonnaise
* several Tablespoon red or green onion, finely minced
* 1 stalk celery, finely minced
* 2 Tablespoon fresh parsley, minced
* 1-2 Tablespoon Dijon mustard
* dash salt and pepper
* 6 hard-boiled eggs, peeled

h3. Method

If you're going to eat the egg salad right away, you can use the eggs while
they're still warm. Otherwise, let them cool first.

Combine everything but eggs. Chop the eggs, stir into mayonnaise mixture, and
serve or refrigerate.
